ation of the text. For each period of history, the important figures and dominant trends, along with exceptions, are identified. The interplay between using and criticising the Bible is explored, as well as how the respective emphasis on these two approaches rises and falls in different periods and locations. The study critically engages with existing scholarship, scrutinizing received views on the subject, and shedding light on an important area of interfaith concern.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aBibelrezeption. 4aHeilige Texte. 4aInterreligiöser Dialog. 4aIslam. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh  aIslam.  aNew Testament.  aOld Testament.  abiblical reception.  ainterreligious dialogue.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2021z978311075072008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCz978311065906108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020 Englishz978311070477808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020z9783110704570oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831103892720 cprintz978311033494440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311033588040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110335880423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110335880/original  a978-3-11-065906-1  De Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCb2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACK